      <hedline>
        <hl1>Miscellany</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>AT&amp;T launches advertising campaign to promote Unity calling plan aimed at connecting wireless and land line customers; ads are BBDO Worldwide's first work for company since AT&amp;T's acquisition of BellSouth (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>AT&amp;T is starting a campaign to promote a new Unity calling plan intended to forge closer ties between its wireless and land line customers. The ads are the first work for AT&amp;T from BBDO Worldwide, part of the Omnicom Group, which was the agency for Cingular Wireless. BBDO became an AT&amp;T agency after the AT&amp;T acquisition of BellSouth, which shared ownership of Cingular with AT&amp;T.</p>
      </block>
